  "text": "For personal use only. on [CITATION_1] . by guest www.bloodjournal.org From 4 inactivation of Hif-p4h-2 does not increase serum Epo or blood hematocrit values. [CITATION_2] We have generated Hif-p4h-2 hypomorphic mice (Hif-p4h-2 gt/gt ) that express lower amounts of wild-type Hifp4h-2 mRNA in various tissues, about 35% of that in wild-type mice in the kidney and 85% in the liver. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] We have also produced P4h-tm -/-mice. These have a mild kidney defect that leads to slight late-onset proteinuria and eye abnormalities that are only seen from about one year onwards (M. R., P. Tiainen, J. Hyvärinen, R.",
